The article discusses the recent press briefing by White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest. The briefing covers a range of topics including the resignation of Secretary of Defense Chuck Hagel, the extension of nuclear talks with Iran, and the upcoming announcement of the grand jury decision in the Ferguson case. Earnest explains that Hagel's resignation was a mutual decision between him and the President, based on the changing priorities and challenges facing the Department of Defense. He also states that the extension of the Iran talks was necessary to allow more time for negotiations and that the President will not support new sanctions at this time. Earnest emphasizes that the President expects the next Secretary of Defense to have strong leadership skills and experience in managing the Department of Defense. Finally, he mentions that the President will address the grand jury decision in Ferguson in a peaceful and respectful manner.